The phrase “subtexit arundine linum’', 110, recalls Ecl. i. 102. Even in his didactic poem Nautica (i. 28-29) Giannettasius has an echo of Sannazaro’s fragment (ll-12) :

mediisque te fluctibus aemula Doris compellat, campusque sonat late omnis aquarum.
